======================================================================
ANALYSIS 1: THE 4-VERTEX SUB-TOURNAMENT REVERSAL
======================================================================

  Case 1:
    Flipped edges: [(1, 2), (1, 3), (1, 5), (2, 3), (2, 5), (3, 5)]
    Vertices involved: [1, 2, 3, 5]
    C(4,2) = 6
    Number of flips: 6
    => ALL edges among [1, 2, 3, 5] are flipped!
    => This is a COMPLETE SUB-TOURNAMENT REVERSAL on [1, 2, 3, 5]

    Sub-tournament on [1, 2, 3, 5] in A1' (H=109):
      v=1: [0, 1, 1, 0]
      v=2: [0, 0, 1, 1]
      v=3: [0, 0, 0, 1]
      v=5: [1, 0, 0, 0]
      Scores: [2, 2, 1, 1]
    Sub-tournament on [1, 2, 3, 5] in A2 (H=111):
      v=1: [0, 0, 0, 1]
      v=2: [1, 0, 0, 0]
      v=3: [1, 1, 0, 0]
      v=5: [0, 1, 1, 0]
      Scores: [1, 1, 2, 2]
    Score reversal: [2, 2, 1, 1] vs [2, 2, 1, 1] (complement)
    => YES, exact complement!

    Directed 3-cycles in sub: A1'=1, A2=1
    Directed 4-cycles in sub: A1'=1, A2=1
    A1' (H=109) sub-scores: [1, 1, 2, 2] (NEAR-REGULAR, 2 directed 3-cycles)
    A2 (H=111) sub-scores: [1, 1, 2, 2] (NEAR-REGULAR, 2 directed 3-cycles)

  Case 2:
    Flipped edges: [(0, 4), (0, 5), (0, 6), (4, 5), (4, 6), (5, 6)]
    Vertices involved: [0, 4, 5, 6]
    C(4,2) = 6
    Number of flips: 6
    => ALL edges among [0, 4, 5, 6] are flipped!
    => This is a COMPLETE SUB-TOURNAMENT REVERSAL on [0, 4, 5, 6]

    Sub-tournament on [0, 4, 5, 6] in A1' (H=109):
      v=0: [0, 1, 0, 0]
      v=4: [0, 0, 1, 1]
      v=5: [1, 0, 0, 1]
      v=6: [1, 0, 0, 0]
      Scores: [1, 2, 2, 1]
    Sub-tournament on [0, 4, 5, 6] in A2 (H=111):
      v=0: [0, 0, 1, 1]
      v=4: [1, 0, 0, 0]
      v=5: [0, 1, 0, 0]
      v=6: [0, 1, 1, 0]
      Scores: [2, 1, 1, 2]
    Score reversal: [1, 2, 2, 1] vs [1, 2, 2, 1] (complement)
    => YES, exact complement!

    Directed 3-cycles in sub: A1'=1, A2=1
    Directed 4-cycles in sub: A1'=1, A2=1
    A1' (H=109) sub-scores: [1, 1, 2, 2] (NEAR-REGULAR, 2 directed 3-cycles)
    A2 (H=111) sub-scores: [1, 1, 2, 2] (NEAR-REGULAR, 2 directed 3-cycles)

