ANALYSIS 2: WHY DOES REVERSAL PRESERVE LAMBDA?
======================================================================

  Case 1:
    S = [1, 2, 3, 5], outside = [0, 4, 6]
    3-cycle status CHANGED: [1, 2, 0], old=False, new=True
    3-cycle status CHANGED: [1, 2, 4], old=True, new=False
    3-cycle status CHANGED: [1, 5, 0], old=True, new=False
    3-cycle status CHANGED: [1, 5, 4], old=False, new=True
    3-cycle status CHANGED: [2, 3, 0], old=True, new=False
    3-cycle status CHANGED: [2, 3, 4], old=False, new=True
    3-cycle status CHANGED: [3, 5, 0], old=False, new=True
    3-cycle status CHANGED: [3, 5, 4], old=True, new=False
    Lambda preserved: True

    Detailed 3-cycle changes for pairs in S with outside vertices:
      w=0: 4 changes
        pair (1, 2): trans->cycle
        pair (1, 5): cycle->trans
        pair (2, 3): cycle->trans
        pair (3, 5): trans->cycle
      w=4: 4 changes
        pair (1, 2): cycle->trans
        pair (1, 5): trans->cycle
        pair (2, 3): trans->cycle
        pair (3, 5): cycle->trans
      w=6: NO changes

  Case 2:
    S = [0, 4, 5, 6], outside = [1, 2, 3]
    3-cycle status CHANGED: [0, 4, 1], old=False, new=True
    3-cycle status CHANGED: [0, 4, 2], old=True, new=False
    3-cycle status CHANGED: [0, 6, 1], old=True, new=False
    3-cycle status CHANGED: [0, 6, 2], old=False, new=True
    3-cycle status CHANGED: [4, 5, 1], old=True, new=False
    3-cycle status CHANGED: [4, 5, 2], old=False, new=True
    3-cycle status CHANGED: [5, 6, 1], old=False, new=True
    3-cycle status CHANGED: [5, 6, 2], old=True, new=False
    Lambda preserved: True

    Detailed 3-cycle changes for pairs in S with outside vertices:
      w=1: 4 changes
        pair (0, 4): trans->cycle
        pair (0, 6): cycle->trans
        pair (4, 5): cycle->trans
        pair (5, 6): trans->cycle
      w=2: 4 changes
        pair (0, 4): cycle->trans
        pair (0, 6): trans->cycle
        pair (4, 5): trans->cycle
        pair (5, 6): cycle->trans
      w=3: NO changes

