ANALYSIS 3: LAMBDA-PRESERVING TRANSFORMATIONS
======================================================================

  Checking all C(7,4)=35 sub-tournament reversals of A2 (bits=4658):
    Original: H=111, c7=9
    Lambda-preserving 4-vertex reversals: 1 out of 35
      S=(1, 2, 3, 5): H=109 (delta=-2), c7=8 (delta=-1)

  Checking all C(7,3)=35 sub-tournament reversals (3-vertex):
    Lambda-preserving 3-vertex reversals: 0 out of 35

======================================================================
ANALYSIS 4: THEORY OF LAMBDA-PRESERVING REVERSALS
======================================================================

THEOREM (Lambda-preservation condition):

Reversing all arcs within S preserves lambda iff for EVERY pair (u,v) in S:
  #{w outside S: v->w and w->u} = #{w outside S: u->w and w->v}

Equivalently, for every (u,v) in S:
  The number of outside vertices w forming a 3-cycle u->v->w->u
  equals the number forming a 3-cycle v->u->w->v.

This is a BALANCE CONDITION: the two orientations of the arc u<->v
participate in equally many 3-cycles with outside vertices.

  Verification for Case 1 (H=111), S=[1, 2, 3, 5], outside=[0, 4, 6]:
    (1,2): fwd_3cyc=1, rev_3cyc=1, balanced=True
    (1,3): fwd_3cyc=0, rev_3cyc=0, balanced=True
    (1,5): fwd_3cyc=1, rev_3cyc=1, balanced=True
    (2,3): fwd_3cyc=1, rev_3cyc=1, balanced=True
    (2,5): fwd_3cyc=0, rev_3cyc=0, balanced=True
    (3,5): fwd_3cyc=1, rev_3cyc=1, balanced=True

======================================================================
ANALYSIS 5: PREVALENCE AT n=7
======================================================================
  Tested: 16384 tournaments
  With at least one lambda-preserving 4-reversal: 3640 (22.2%)
  Total reversals: 5200 (avg 0.32 per tournament)

======================================================================
ANALYSIS 6: VITALI ATOMS AND H-CHANGE
======================================================================
  Delta H distribution:
    delta_H = +0: 5200 occurrences

  Delta c7 distribution:
    delta_c7 = +0: 5200 occurrences

  Is delta_H = 2*delta_c7 always?

Since lambda is preserved, the 3-cycle vertex sets are preserved.
Therefore c3, c5, alpha_2 are ALL preserved.
The OCF decomposition gives: H = 1 + 2*(c3+c5+c7) + 4*alpha_2
So delta_H = 2*delta_c7 ALWAYS.

This means the Vitali atom changes H by exactly 2*delta_c7.
The minimal non-trivial change is delta_c7 = +/-1, giving delta_H = +/-2.


